# IP Freely
This is a program that takes an IP in IPv4 format and pings all available addresses on the network.

## Overview
This program will
- Take the provided IP and find the Network address
- From the network address, it will find the host address
- Once the host address is found, it will calculate the highest and lowest IP available on your network
- It will then loop through each available address, ping each one, and return the responses from each address
- If a response is received, it will check specified ports to see if they are running


## Requirements
- Python 3+
- An internet connection

## How to Run
1. Clone this repo by running `git clone https://github.com/WTCSC/ip-freely-Fooot-Code.git` in a terminal
2. Type `python3 ip_freely.py [IP_ADDRESS]` to run the python file. Make sure to type the IP Address in IPv4 format with a subnet mask attached in CIDR format (i.e. 10.103.0.63/23)
3. You can also supply a port(s) to scan by running `python3 ip_freely.py -p [PORT_TO_SCAN] [IP_ADDRESS]` which will then check if the ports at the specific IP address is open. Inputs can look like "80" for 1 port, "22,80,3306" for multiple ports, or "1-1000" for a range of ports
4. Wait while the program pings every available ip address, and displays their status.
5. The program will then prompt the user to see if they would like a summary. This will allow them to see only IPs that are up.